args:
The prince's group hides in the mountains.
Pinon reveals that her superior informed her
that Faris is a traitor, and that she was on a
a secret mission to keep the sealing stone away
from him. The apostle Basileus then rushes onto
the scene, proclaiming that he will stop Faris.
Well, that escalated quickly.\nWho could have committed that murder?
It...might have been Faris,\njust like the villagers said.
Pinon, please don't say such\ndreadful things!
I agree, Little Pi. I can't believe you\nwould doubt a comrade-in-arms.
There's actually something I've been hiding\nfrom you all. Before going undercover in\nParadise, I was summoned by Regina.
The commander of the apostles, and the\none whose Sigil ties her to Sandalphon.\nShe's my Little Pi's superior.
During the wroth incident caused by a\nsealing stone in the south, a priest was\nthe culprit.

Regina was concerned that there might
be other dissident elements within the
Church, so she launched a clandestine
internal investigation.
It was then that she determined there\nwas one individual plotting to revive a\ndemon. And that individual was...Faris.

If Madame's power does happen to spring
from a sealing stone, then Faris may use
recovering it as a pretext to obtain it
for himself.
It was with those concerns that Regina\ngave me my orders.
I was told to confirm the presence of a\nsealing stone in Paradise, and to keep its\npresence a secret from Faris.
That's why I lied when I inspected Madame\nand said she didn't have one.
So she really DID have one.
And that's why you suggested that we\nwrap up the investigation early—all to\nconceal its existence from Faris.
Hold on, Little Pi. I haven't heard\nof any such orders from Regina.
It was a secret mission that she handed\ndown to me alone.
Even so, I would have thought you'd\nhave at least told me of all people...
I'm no longer a helpless child, Gabriel.
I'm an apostle who will fulfill her duty,\neven if I must do so alone.
That's not what I—oh, my dear Little Pi...
Faris, a traitor? The idea doesn't just strike\nme as implausible, but utterly bizarre...
He has more pride than anyone in our work\nas apostles. He would never, ever betray\nthe Church!
Try to calm down, Ryszarda.\nAll we have to do is confirm\nwhat Pinon said for ourselves.
Angels can speak to each other\ntelepathically even when they're\nfar apart, right?
Indeed. I will contact Sandalphon and\nreport in with information about the current\nsituation.
I can't speak to Sandalphon. Some kind\nof magic or something is blocking me\nfrom doing so.
What the—?! Who are these people?!
Could these be the Templars who went\nmissing in Paradise?
Bringing the hammer of divine justice\ndown on the heads of you miscreants\ndisturbing the peace!
Did Madame rewrite their memories\nand make them into her allies?
Hrk! Such strength...\nEven I can't push them back!
We're surrounded.\nThere's nowhere to run...\nThis is not looking good!
Gloried Templars of the church,\nseduced by miasma? Shameful.
Hmph. That takes care of them.\nAre you all unharmed?

I am the apostle Basileus—an ally of
Pinon and the others. You must be the one
I read of in the reports documenting the
wroth incident: {player_name}.
Thank you for your help, Basileus!\nBut why are you here?
Orders from Regina. I was also informed\nof Faris's betrayal and sent to quell his\nwicked scheme.
I dropped by the town just before\ncoming here and examined the murder\nvictim's corpse.
I found, in addition to a laceration\ncaused by a bladed weapon, a wound that\nappeared to be from a manacaster round.

No mere villager would be in possession
of something so sophisticated as a
manacaster. And the only one here
now who DOES have such a weapon...

The corpse was assaulted with a knife
to draw attention away from the caster
wound. Mere artifice. The girl must have
learned something she wasn't meant to.
No... This isn't possible.\nFaris would never...

There is other circumstantial evidence.
I have detected a sort of special barrier
erected here that disrupts the telepathic
communications between angels.
Which is why I wasn't able to get in\ntouch with Sandalphon.
Only an apostle would have the\nrequisite grasp of angelic capabilities\nto create such an impediment.
To be sure, Faris does seem suspicious\nwhen you consider the situation...
I WANT to believe in his innocence.\nBut we are apostles.

We must accept the reality before us and
take the appropriate countermeasures.
Even if the reality is that our friends are
actually our enemies.
So what ought we do now?
Faris is shrewd. By now, he'll have\nrealized that you were telling a lie.
If his objective is indeed the sealing stone,\nhe'll have to show his face near Madame\neventually.
We'll keep watch around her and\nwait for Faris to make his move.
{player_name}, the fight ahead\nis for us apostles alone to settle.\nI urge you to return to your journey.
I've helped out this long. I'm going to see\nthis through with you all 'til the end.
Hm... Very well. I'm grateful for your aid.
